</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>ACR67:v97#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="ACR67"/><meta name="dc:title" content="ACR &#xA;              67-&#xA;                CHAPTERED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div width="100%" style="text-align:center;"><div id="bill_num_title_chap"><span style="text-align:center;font-weight:bold;font-size:1.1em;font-family:'Times New Roman'; "><b>
                Assembly Concurrent Resolution
              
                        No. 67</b></span></div><div style="text-align:center;padding-top: 1.0em;padding-bottom: 1.2em;" id="chap_num_title_chap"><span style="font-size:1.4em;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;">
                      CHAPTER 96</span></div></div><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to Stronger Starts for Children Day. </span></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center">
                  
                  [<span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Filed with
              </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Secretary of State
              </span> <span style="font-size: 13pt">June 25, 2025.
                      </span>]
                </div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">ACR 67, Sharp-Collins.
                          Stronger Starts for Children Day.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would declare May 10, 2025, as Stronger Starts for Children Day in California.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_4C6AB69C-D422-4550-932F-B4C59726A267"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, For the last 25 years, First 5 California’s focus has been to help children 0 to five years of age receive the best start in life by advancing trauma-informed, healing-centered, and culturally responsive care systems; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_ABDA9005-5379-4F7A-BF78-069049E79C24"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, In partnership with 58 county commissions in California, First 5 California’s goal is that within one generation, all children will have access to safe, stable, nurturing relationships and environments to achieve healthy development; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_D9EE6CBE-1B4D-4E28-9A54-3AF829E014AB"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Stronger Starts is a First 5 California campaign launched on June 1, 2023, that aims to educate California parents about the impact of adverse childhood experiences (ACEs) and toxic stress response (TSR) in young children; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_856C3336-CB03-49C8-BAE9-3F5A16708FC3"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, ACEs are severe adversities experienced by children when prenatal through 18 years of age, ranging from household dysfunction through systemic issues, such as abuse, neglect, loss of a parent, lack of food or shelter, racism, bullying, witnessing violence, or other harsh experiences that can result in childhood trauma; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_F71788BF-4AF9-4061-AB4C-D8D4D6D3456C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Toxic stress response is what occurs in children when they are affected by ACEs and has a long-term impact on their health and wellness, including high blood pressure, diabetes, asthma, anxiety, depression, and developmental delays; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_B6E3A6AA-A850-4929-9A70-620B9630B5F3"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, ACEs and toxic stress severely impact a child’s development when prenatal through five years old, when 90 percent of the brain is developing and one million neural pathways are forming every second; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_8793EA4B-6F97-45F6-A7BB-7E6DF11D7DA3"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, In California, nearly two million children are impacted by ACEs, putting them at risk for health, behavioral, and learning problems; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_35461DB4-BB00-4B47-AC65-C0EDD9139E19"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Young children who are continuously exposed to ACEs without adequate buffering protections, particularly during the critical periods of early development, can develop a biological effect, known as toxic stress response; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_4442E217-1F28-4883-83AA-B882F1527B63"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, According to a recent survey, a remarkable 87 to 93 percent of caregivers intend to take action to manage toxic stress in themselves and their children, a vital precursor to long-term behavior change upon receiving information via the Stronger Starts campaign; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_2BB031A1-1539-45DF-A6C0-A95C29D5C9F9"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, ACEs and toxic stress can be prevented by creating and sustaining safe, stable, and nurturing relationships and environments (SSNREs) for children; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_A7C1D7AA-2536-4D12-AA3C-77DA926F0A6F"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The State of California could save upwards of $1.5 billion in annual health costs if more parents and caregivers were made aware of ACEs and TSR in children; now, therefore, be it </div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_65A4851D-E6C2-46B1-A464-C4093A78BF09"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Assembly of the State of California, the Senate thereof concurring, That the Legislature declares May 10, 2025, as Stronger Starts for Children Day in California and commits itself to the advancement of health and well-being for all children and families through First 5 California’s Stronger Starts campaign; and be it further </div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_098082C8-B089-432D-86DD-ABBEE8C95E08"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
